 from his chair and walked to the window.";i:10;s:49:"At a university a chair is the post of professor.";i:11;s:69:"He gave London University 600000 to establish a chair in Islamic art.";i:12;s:81:"A seat for one person that has a back usually four legs and sometimes two arms 2.";i:13;s:54:"Occasional chairs can be used in any room in the home.";i:14;s:129:"Whether for a bedroom living room bathroom basement games room or a dining area the chair can fulfil a variety of roles and uses.";i:15;s:156:"As an exact definition an occasional chair is more of a concept rather than a standard design type and this means that in the right circumstances any style.";i:16;s:49:"English Language Learners Definition of chairman.";i:17;s:77:"The person especially a man who is in charge of a meeting committee or event.";i:18;s:57:"The person who is in charge of a company or organization.";i:19;s:63:"Who knew that the chair had such a strange and winding history.";i:20;s:195:"It has gone from its earliest uses as a mark of distinction reserved for Kings and Priests to being a mainstay of modern life and something essential for the proper functioning of modern society.";i:21;s:27:"Definition of chair noun 1.";i:22;s:67:"A separate seat for one person typically with a back and four legs.";i:23;s:112:"The person in charge of a meeting or of an organization used as a neutral alternative to chairman or chairwoman.";i:24;s:67:"Shes the chair of a research committee - the post of a chairperson.";i:25;s:62:"He was due to step down after a three-year stint in the chair.";i:26;s:208:"Placed across from a bed a slipper chair can offer a useful place to perch when putting on shoes catching up on a bit of reading or passing time while waiting for your certain someone to finish getting ready.";i:27;s:131:"Cozy a side table up to a slipper chair and youve procured a functional corner out of awkward space that might otherwise go unused.";i:28;s:54:"Two slipper chairs can also be dropped at the foot of.";i:29;s:173:"The quote explains that professors hold a chair which captures the why and explains the subtle differences between different usages of the term which captures correct usage.";i:30;s:51:"So it seems to me that it does answer the question.";i:31;s:101:"A chair for use by an infant disabled person etc when learning to walk or for support during walking.";i:32;s:189:"2 The person in charge of a meeting or of an organization used as a neutral alternative to chairman or chairwoman The princess is the chair of the sister organization in the United Kingdom.";i:33;s:84:"Members will choose a new chair during the next meeting scheduled for November 17th.";i:34;s:25:"Definition of CHAIR verb.";i:35;s:37:"Be in charge of meeting or committee.";i:36;s:93:"Definition and synonyms of chair from the online English dictionary from Macmillan Education.";i:37;s:89:"This is the British English definition of chairView American English definition of chair.";i:38;s:51:"Change your default dictionary to American English.";i:39;s:95:"Accent chairs are chairs that are placed strategically in a room to provide additional seating.";i:40;s:58:"There are two approaches to making use of an accent chair.";i:41;s:133:"One approach is to place the chair in a position that complements or accents the colors and textures of larger pieces such as a sofa.";i:42;s:57:"A second approach to the use of this type of chair is to.";i:43;s:79:"Historically an accent or occasional chair is meant for use every now and then.";i:44;s:79:"This means they can be upholstered in a more expensive or more delicate fabric.";i:45;s:128:"Although often used in living spaces to accommodate extra guests they are also found in bedrooms used as a place to put clothes.";i:46;s:54:"A shower chair is a seat made for bathtubs or showers.";i:47;s:105:"These seats are designed for use by people who are unable to stand to take a shower and must sit instead.";i:48;s:116:"With the use of shower chairs elderly people and those with mobility problems are able to have some independence by.";i:49;s:60:"A chair is a seat with four legs and a back to lean against.";i:50;s:102:"When you invite a large group for dinner you have to make sure you find chairs for all of your guests.";i:51;s:202:"A wheelchair is a manually operated or power-driven device designed primarily for use by an individual with a mobility disability for the main purpose of indoor or of both indoor and outdoor locomotion.";i:52;s:137:"Individuals with mobility disabilities must be permitted to use wheelchairs and manually powered mobility aids ie walkers crutches canes.";}}